<task id="AIPU2-021" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build GroundednessCheckService — Hallucination Detection</title>
    <phase>2B</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai-safety, groundedness</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-003, AIPU2-006</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Build GroundednessCheckService, which calls the Azure AI Content Safety Groundedness Detection API after
    each LLM response to identify claims that are not supported by the retrieved source documents. Unlike
    PromptShield (which blocks before the LLM), groundedness checking is non-blocking — ungrounded segments
    are flagged and annotated in the SSE stream (as a safety_annotation event) rather than suppressed. This
    allows the user to see AI output while being informed of which parts lack document support. Latency budget
    is under 200ms and runs in parallel with the streaming response where possible.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET backend engineer with Azure AI Content Safety and SSE streaming experience.</role>
  <goal>
    After each LLM response, ungrounded claim segments are identified via the Groundedness Detection API and
    emitted as a safety_annotation SSE event. The check completes in under 200ms and is non-blocking.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/ai.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/auth-AI-azure-resources.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read AI-ARCHITECTURE.md to understand the current SSE streaming pipeline and where post-LLM processing hooks exist.</step>
    <step>Create IGroundednessCheckService.cs interface with: Task&lt;GroundednessResult&gt; CheckAsync(GroundednessRequest request, CancellationToken ct).</step>
    <step>Create GroundednessRequest.cs record: LlmResponse (string — full text of AI answer), SourceDocuments (IReadOnlyList&lt;string&gt; — retrieved passage texts).</step>
    <step>Create GroundednessResult.cs record: IsGrounded (bool), UngroundedSegments (IReadOnlyList&lt;UngroundedSegment&gt;), LatencyMs (double). Create UngroundedSegment record: Text (string), Reason (string?).</step>
    <step>Create GroundednessCheckService.cs implementing IGroundednessCheckService. Use named HttpClient "ContentSafety" (same as PromptShield). Call POST https://{endpoint}/contentsafety/text:detectGroundedness?api-version=2024-09-15 with body { "domain": "generic", "task": "QnA", "qna": { "query": "...", "answer": llmResponse }, "groundingSources": sourceDocuments }.</step>
    <step>Parse response: extract ungroundedDetected and ungroundedDetails[].text. Build GroundednessResult. If SourceDocuments is empty, skip the API call and return IsGrounded = true (no sources to check against).</step>
    <step>Handle failure modes: timeout (&gt;200ms), HTTP 429, HTTP 5xx → return GroundednessResult with IsGrounded = true and log warning (non-blocking, fail-safe).</step>
    <step>Emit safety_annotation SSE event after the main response stream completes (or concurrently if the streaming pipeline supports it). Event payload: { "type": "groundedness", "isGrounded": bool, "ungroundedSegments": [...] }.</step>
    <step>Register IGroundednessCheckService in AddAiSafetyModule(). Emit OTEL counter ai_safety_groundedness_ungrounded_total and histogram ai_safety_groundedness_latency_ms.</step>
    <step>Write unit tests: ungrounded response → segments returned, fully grounded → empty segments, empty sources → skipped (IsGrounded=true), timeout → fail-safe IsGrounded=true.</step>
    <step>Run `dotnet build` and `dotnet test --filter "Groundedness"` to verify.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Ungrounded segments identified by the API are included in GroundednessResult.UngroundedSegments.</criterion>
    <criterion>safety_annotation SSE event emitted after each LLM response with groundedness data.</criterion>
    <criterion>Service completes in under 200ms (P95).</criterion>
    <criterion>Empty source document list causes the check to be skipped (returns IsGrounded = true).</criterion>
    <criterion>API failures result in fail-safe behavior (IsGrounded = true, warning logged) — never blocks the response.</criterion>
    <criterion>OTEL counter and histogram emitted correctly.</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests pass: `dotnet test --filter "Groundedness"`.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
